vllm-shim local patch: use hipBLASLt's matmul heuristic API to bound
AITER's per-shape kernel candidate set, instead of enumerating every
algorithm hipBLASLt knows about.

`hipblasLtMatmul_findallsols_wrapper` in gradlib/csrc/hipbsolgemm.cu
currently calls `hipblaslt_ext::getAllAlgos` to enumerate all kernels
for the given GemmType + dtype tuple, ignoring the actual matmul
descriptor (m, n, k, layouts, bias, scaling). For a typical fp8/bf16
matmul on MI300X this returns ~1365 candidates, and the cheap
`matmulIsAlgoSupported` filter that follows only checks workspace
fit; it does not rank. The tuner then benchmarks every surviving
candidate, which is both slow and includes algorithms that fault
the GPU on specific shape geometries (the root cause of the
mp_tuner KeyError storms that the adjacent mp_tuner patch
papers over).

`hipblasLtMatmulAlgoGetHeuristic` was the original code path here
(now commented out on the line immediately above the getAllAlgos
call) and is the right shape: it uses the full matmul descriptor to
filter and rank candidates by predicted performance, then returns
the top N. The commented-out version is not drop-in functional
because the `preference` object and `returnedAlgoCount` int it
references were removed alongside it; this patch creates both.

The candidate cap is read from the environment so operators can
dial it without rebuilding the image. Default 10 matches the
original code's hardcoded N. Set `AITER_MAX_GEMM_CANDIDATES=2048`
to effectively recover the full sweep behavior.

There is no known upstream PR for this change. The shim's Docker
images carry it locally until upstream lands an equivalent knob.
The image-baked cache-key in /etc/vllm-shim/aiter-cache-key picks
up the change automatically: the SHA of the patches directory
moves, so `AITER_JIT_DIR` namespaces under a fresh `jit-<key>`
subdir and AITER recompiles the patched .so on first call instead
of loading a stale cached binary from the PV.

--- a/gradlib/csrc/hipbsolgemm.cu
+++ b/gradlib/csrc/hipbsolgemm.cu
@@ -230,21 +230,33 @@
             matmul, HIPBLASLT_MATMUL_DESC_D_SCALE_POINTER, &scaleC, sizeof(scaleC)));
     }
 
-    // std::vector<hipblasLtMatmulHeuristicResult_t> heuristicResult(10);
-    // CHECK_HIPBLAS_ERROR(hipblasLtMatmulAlgoGetHeuristic(
-    //     handle, matmul, matA, matB, matC, matC,
-    //     preference, 10, heuristicResult.data(), &returnedAlgoCount));
-    std::vector<hipblasLtMatmulHeuristicResult_t> heuristicResult;
-    CHECK_HIPBLAS_ERROR(hipblaslt_ext::getAllAlgos(handle,
-                                                   hipblaslt_ext::GemmType::HIPBLASLT_GEMM,
-                                                   op_A,
-                                                   op_B,
-                                                   intype,
-                                                   intype,
-                                                   outtype,
-                                                   outtype,
-                                                   HIPBLAS_COMPUTE_32F,
-                                                   heuristicResult));
+    // vllm-shim patch: use hipBLASLt's matmul heuristic to get the
+    // top-N ranked algorithms for this specific shape/dtype/layout
+    // instead of the full ~1365 candidates from getAllAlgos. The
+    // heuristic uses the matmul descriptor (m/n/k, layouts, bias,
+    // scaling) to filter and rank; benchmarking ranked candidates
+    // for each shape avoids the long tail of algos that fault on
+    // specific geometries. Cap is configurable via env var so an
+    // operator can dial it without rebuilding the image.
+    int max_candidates = 10;
+    if (const char* env = std::getenv("AITER_MAX_GEMM_CANDIDATES")) {
+        int parsed = std::atoi(env);
+        if (parsed > 0) {
+            max_candidates = parsed;
+        }
+    }
+    hipblasLtMatmulPreference_t preference;
+    CHECK_HIPBLAS_ERROR(hipblasLtMatmulPreferenceCreate(&preference));
+    CHECK_HIPBLAS_ERROR(hipblasLtMatmulPreferenceSetAttribute(
+        preference, HIPBLASLT_MATMUL_PREF_MAX_WORKSPACE_BYTES,
+        &workspace_size, sizeof(workspace_size)));
+    std::vector<hipblasLtMatmulHeuristicResult_t> heuristicResult(max_candidates);
+    int returnedAlgoCount = 0;
+    CHECK_HIPBLAS_ERROR(hipblasLtMatmulAlgoGetHeuristic(
+        handle, matmul, matA, matB, matC, matC,
+        preference, max_candidates, heuristicResult.data(), &returnedAlgoCount));
+    heuristicResult.resize(returnedAlgoCount);
+    CHECK_HIPBLAS_ERROR(hipblasLtMatmulPreferenceDestroy(preference));
 
     std::vector<int> algoIndex;
     int returned_algo_count = heuristicResult.size();
